UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304405X15001191
KW  - Dark pool
KW  - Price discovery
KW  - Efficiency
AB  - Regulators globally are concerned that dark trading harms price discovery. We show that dark trades are less informed than lit trades. High levels of dark trading increase adverse selection risk on the lit exchange by increasing the concentration of informed traders. Using both high- and low-frequency measures of informational efficiency we find that low levels of non-block dark trading are benign or even beneficial for informational efficiency, but high levels are harmful. In contrast, we find no evidence that block trades in the dark impede price discovery.
ER  - 

